page.title: 05MY FAVOURITE KEELBY PLACES
page.content: My name is Emma Gresswell I am 10 years old. My favourite places in Keelby are Trolls Bridge and the Dead End. I like Trolls Bridge because when the fields surrounding it are nice and golden with corn you can go on picnics. There is quite a small stream running under Trolls Bridge but it is enjoyable to watch . My brother and I sometimes go fishing with a fishing net but we don't catch much. We did go down there once though and I managed to catch an extremeley big toad . We also got some water insects . The stream has got lots of vegetation growing in it but people like putting litter in it . It is fairly deep and if you walk in it you get stuck in the mud.The Dead End is also an enjoyable place to be because you can have secret dens down there .My friends and I often play action packed games there
